Durban - The festive season road safety report 2018/2019 will be released by the South African Transport minister on Friday. Dr. Blade Nzimande, the Minister of Transport will officially release the preliminary report at the Durban International Convention Centre (ICC) in Durban. The report covers the period from December 1, 2018 to January 8, 2019. Nzimande will be joined by MECs for Transport and Community Safety in the provinces, Board Chairpersons and CEOs of Transport entities, key transport stakeholders and senior government officials. When Nzimande released the mid-festive season road safety report on DecemberÂ  20, 2018, a total 767 fatalities had been recorded, indicating a 16% increase on the same period in 2017. The Road Traffic Management Corporation has said that by mid December, the number of fatalities on KZN roads stood at 160. Spokesperson Simon Zwane said the final figures across the country would be released once schools opened. Daily News